Source-Makefile: package/network/utils/iftop/Makefile
Package: iftop
Version: 1.0pre2-1
Depends: +libc +USE_GLIBC:librt +USE_GLIBC:libpthread +libpcap +libncurses +libpthread
Menu-Depends: 
Provides: 
Section: net
Category: Network
Title: display bandwith usage on an interface
Maintainer: Jo-Philipp Wich <jow@openwrt.org>
Source: iftop-1.0pre2.tar.gz
Type: ipkg
Description: 	iftop does for network usage what top(1) does for CPU usage. It 
	listens to network traffic on a named interface and displays a 
	table of current bandwidth usage by pairs of hosts. Handy for 
	answering the question 'why is our ADSL link so slow?'.
http://www.ex-parrot.com/~pdw/iftop/
Jo-Philipp Wich <jow@openwrt.org>
@@


