Source-Makefile: package/network/ipv6/6relayd/Makefile
Package: 6relayd
Version: 2012-12-27-09f0cf6d6c7fcae7393e4aeecabc3e204cd98366
Depends: +libc +USE_GLIBC:librt +USE_GLIBC:libpthread +kmod-ipv6
Menu-Depends: 
Provides: 
Section: ipv6
Category: IPv6
Title: IPv6-Relay and Server (RD-, DHCPv6- & NDP-Proxy)
Maintainer: Steven Barth <steven@midlink.org>
Source: 6relayd-2012-12-27.tar.bz2
Type: ipkg
Description:  6relayd is an IPv6-tool that relays IPv6-management protocols like router
 discovery, neighbor discovery and DHCPv6 so that clients on routed (non-
 bridged) interfaces can use the public address prefix, DHCPv6 and DNS-service
 of a master interface. This is useful to avoid NAT in chained IPv6-routers.

 It can also be used as a lightweight router advertisement daemon and provide
 stateless DHCPv6 service where size matters.
Steven Barth <steven@midlink.org>
@@


